  "texts": [
    "SummaryAlthough the model-based methods have been well investigated with a solid theoretical basis, they may encounter some obstacles in practical deployment, such as complexity, availability, and tractability of the model.",
    "AI is a promising technique to deal with these issues because of its outstanding non-linear fitting capability, generalization, and fast inference speed.",
    "Therefore, the AI-based methods are becoming alternatives to the model-based ones for the dynamic and non-linear ISAC systems with high-dimension variables.",
    "AI designs for ISACIn this section, we overview the typical AI designs for different aspects of ISAC, as in Table 9 [ [74][75][76], including parameter estimation, waveform design, predictive beamforming, resource allocation, interference mitigation, and system-level design.",
    "Parameter estimationParameter estimation is a fundamental task of sensing, aiming to obtain the key parameters of the target of interest, such as distance, angle, and velocity."
  ]
}